quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,1,"Kaf. Ha'. Ya'. Ayn. Sad."
  19,2,"This is an account of the mercy of your Lord to His servant Zechariah",footnotes:178985:1,footnotes:178986:2
  19,3,"when he cried to his Lord in secret."
  19,4,"He said: "Lord! My bones have grown feeble and my head is glistening with age; yet, never have my prayers to You, my Lord, been unfruitful."
  19,5,"I fear evil from my kinsmen after I am gone; and my wife is barren, so grant me an heir out of Your special grace,",footnotes:178987:1
  19,6,"one that might be my heir and the heir of the house of Jacob; and make him, Lord, one that will be pleasing to You.",footnotes:178988:1
  19,7,"(He was told): "Zechariah, We bring you the good news of the birth of a son whose name shall be Yahya (John), one whose namesake We never created before."",footnotes:178989:1
  19,8,"He said: "My Lord! How can I have a boy when my wife is barren and I have reached an extremely old age?""
  19,9,"He answered: "So shall it be." Your Lord says: "It is easy for Me," and then added: "For beyond doubt, I created you earlier when you were nothing."",footnotes:178990:1
  19,10,"Zechariah said: "Lord, grant me a Sign." Said He: "Your Sign is that you shall not be able to speak to people for three nights, though you will be otherwise sound.""